==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Liber
<hw>Li"ber</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"b⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
See <er>Libel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The inner bark of
plants, lying next to the wood. It usually contains a large proportion
of woody, fibrous cells, and is, therefore, the part from which the
fiber of the plant is obtained, as that of hemp, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Liber cells</b></col>, <cd>elongated woody cells found in
the liber.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liberal</ent>⟦br⟧
